Pietermaritzburg - A man, believed to be in his 30s, was seriously wounded in a shooting incident at a taxi rank on Pietermaritz Road in Pietermaritzburg on Saturday morning, KwaZulu-Natal paramedics said.ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene shortly before 7am and found the man laying at the entrance to the taxi rank, surrounded by numerous members of the local authorities, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said.Upon assessment, paramedics discovered that the man had sustained several gunshot wounds, leaving him in a serious condition. Paramedics immediately began their treatment and provided the patient with advanced life support interventions.Once treated, the man was transported to Greys Provincial Hospital for further urgent treatment.The motive for the shooting was not yet known, he said. African News Agency